The company calls it ‘personal authorisation through data’.
The idea behind Inrupt is according to the company’s CEO, John Bruce, that the company should provide resources, processes and relevant competence to make Solid available to all.
The company currently consists of Berners-Lee, Bruce, a security platform purchased by IBM, some contracted developers to work with the project and a bunch of volunteer programmers.
From this week on, technology developers around the world can create their own decentralised apps using the tools available on the Inrupt website.
